The paper deals with algorithms for counting perfect matchings in graphs, which is a topic in both graph theory and computational complexity. The use of graph decompositions and planar graphs suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.CG (computational geometry) sub-categories. The paper also deals with counting problems, which is a topic in cs.DM (discrete mathematics) and cs.CC (computational complexity). Finally, the mention of Pfaffian orientations suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (graph theory) sub-category.
